  "body": "I'm having some issues rendering from server side `select` tags.\n\nIt's possible reproduce the problem with this:\n\n``` jsx\n  return <select value=\"3\">\n              <option value=\"1\">Foo 1</option>\n              <option value=\"2\">Foo 3</option>\n              <option value=\"3\">Foo 3</option>\n         </select>\n```\n\nThe browser interprets the generated DOM by the react server, but cause it's not a `selected` attribute in any `option` tag, it displays the first option, `\"1\"`, as selected. For the time React loads, let's say ~0.5 second, then the correct option is displayed as selected.\n\nDo you think there is a solution for this behaviour?\n",
